Test scenario: JVEWRKB01 - Test Visual Editor interactions with the Eclipse 
workbench

This may be related to bug 46272... similar stack trace.

Setup: ensure you have more than one Java Project.

Select New-->Examples-->AWT/Swing and select the Simple Text Editor example 
create and open a class in the Visual Editor. Drop any bean (e.g. JButton) onto 
the canvas.

From the Package Explorer, select and delete the SimpleTextEditor.java file.
The VE is still open at this point. Select the tab or anywhere in the editor 
and a message prompt will display asking to save or close the editor. Select 
save and specify a different project location.

The canvas goes blank... causes a NullpointerException and an error message to 
look in the log. Here's the exception:
